article.headline: William &amp, Mary 84, Radford 52
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- Matt Rum came off the bench to score 16 points and lead five William & Mary players in double figures as the Tribe rolled past Radford 84-52 on Saturday night. Quinn McDowell added 13 points and 10 rebounds for the Tribe (8-20), who snapped their four-game losing streak and sent Radford (5-22) to its 11th loss in 12 games. William & Mary raced out to a 12-2 lead and then used an 18-3 run to streak its advantage to 32-12. The Tribe led 35-20 at halftime. Rum hit a 3-pointer for a 49-27 lead with 15:41 remaining and followed with another one for a 52-29 advantage with 14:16 to play. The Tribe shot 52.5 percent from the floor (31 of 59). Julian Boatner had 12 points and Brandon Britt and Marcus Kitts had 10 each for William & Mary. Jareal Smith led the Highlanders with 18 points and Tolga Cerrah had his third double-double with 11 points and 15 rebounds.
